[thinking] **Considering exception handling in tests**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm examining the ClassReloadingStrategyTest, which catches the IllegalStateException related to "agent not installed" in native environments. It captures this before hitting an Error, leading to a successful native pass. I wonder if we could implement a similar approach in our tests, but we might miss out on coverage for native cases. Dynamic access coverage likely comes from the JVM, and I might also catch the IllegalStateException if the message indicates "direct dispatcher not available."
